nodes.text: Vinefish were a type of fish creature. Vinefish were grilled by vendors and sold as food near Yinta Lake on the planet Vulta during the time that the smuggler Zeerid Korr was on his way to meet his daughter, Arra Yooms, in the year 3653 BBY. One such vendor attempted to sell Korr some freshly grilled vinefish, but Korr did not buy any.
Vinefish were first mentioned in Paul S. Kemp's novel The Old Republic: Deceived, which was released on March 22, 2011.
